EasyLaseGetCardNum

public static int EasyLaseGetCardNum()
Will return the number of connected cards and opens the devices. Must be used before all other functions!

Returns:
0 = no cards, 1-20 number of cards connected.

EasyLaseWriteFrame

public static boolean EasyLaseWriteFrame(IntByReference CardNumber,
                                         EasylaseUsb2Native.Point.ByReference Datapointer,
                                         int Bytenumber,
                                         short Pointspeed)
Send a frame from @ Datapointer to card number (CardNumber). Maximum framesize is 16.000 points or 128 Kbytes. Value in Bytenumber is number of points in the frame multiplied with 8 Pointspeed is outputspeed in pps and should be between 1000 and 65.535.

Parameters:
CardNumber - 0 – number of cards
Datapointer - The frame
Bytenumber - 0 – 1FFFFh
Pointspeed - 1000 - FFFFh
Returns:
true -> Okay, false -> USB error

EasyLaseWriteFrameNR

public static boolean EasyLaseWriteFrameNR(IntByReference CardNumber,
                                           EasylaseUsb2Native.Point.ByReference Datapointer,
                                           int Bytenumber,
                                           short Pointspeed,
                                           short RepNum)
Send a frame like EasyLaseWriteFrame, but without automatic frame repeat, if there is no new frame following the actual one. Output stops at the last point until new frame comes in.

Parameters:
CardNumber - 0 – number of cards
Datapointer - The frame
Bytenumber - 0 – 1FFFFh
Pointspeed - 1000 - FFFFh
RepNum - 0
Returns:
true -> Okay, false -> USB error

EasyLaseGetStatus

public static int EasyLaseGetStatus(IntByReference CardNumber)
Returns the status of the on board framebuffers.

Parameters:
CardNumber -
Returns:
0 = USB error, 1 = Ready (a new frame can be received), 2 = Busy (all buffers full, incoming frames will be discarded)
